🧩 Step 1 — Install htpasswd (on your EC2 machine)
sudo yum install httpd-tools -y
🧩 Step 2 — Create users file
htpasswd -c -B users.htpasswd student1

Enter password (simple for training)

Add more users:

htpasswd -B users.htpasswd student2
htpasswd -B users.htpasswd student3
...
🧩 Step 3 — Create secret in OpenShift
oc create secret generic htpasswd-secret \
  --from-file=htpasswd=users.htpasswd \
  -n openshift-config
🧩 Step 4 — Configure OAuth
oc edit oauth cluster

Add this under spec:

spec:
  identityProviders:
  - name: htpasswd_provider
    mappingMethod: claim
    type: HTPasswd
    htpasswd:
      fileData:
        name: htpasswd-secret

Save and exit.

🧠 Wait ~1–2 minutes

Now login screen will support your users

🧩 Step 5 — Create project per student
oc new-project student1
oc new-project student2
oc new-project student3
🧩 Step 6 — Assign permissions
oc policy add-role-to-user admin student1 -n student1
oc policy add-role-to-user admin student2 -n student2
